==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: condog
<hw>con*dog"</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[A punning
corruption of con<ets>cur</ets>.]</ety> <def>To concur; to agree.</def>
<mark>[Burlesque]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word appears in early dictionaries as a synonym for
the word <xex>agree</xex>; thus. ⟦ldquo⟧Agree; concurre, cohere,
<xex>condog</xex>, condescend.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Condolatory</ent>⟦br⟧
